						<div class="postbody">I've always wondered why they couldn't just make a sprite 0 hit when it was drawn. I agree it's overly complex that it has to be a solid sprite pixel on a solid BG pixel. I actually have used it for sprite to BG collision in my REALLY newbie crap demos. In real, professional game design this is just plain sloppy. It's great for split screen effects though, assuming you know that the NMI has already happened in the current frame.</div>

					
